sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Operator
    participant UI as sandbox-manager-app
    participant Manager as Manager REST / Protocol layer
    participant Handlers as Manager operation handlers
    participant Supervisor as SandboxSupervisor
    participant Driver as ContainerRuntimeDriver
    participant Agent as sandbox-agent session / runtime
    participant Outbox as /state event outbox
    participant DB as PostgreSQL event and lifecycle stores
    participant Reducers as Browser event reducers

    Operator->>UI: Create a sandbox
    UI->>Manager: Authenticated sandbox.create + idempotency key
    Manager->>Handlers: Validate catalog operation and target
    Handlers->>DB: Materialize volume/config metadata and persist record_created
    Note over UI,Supervisor: sandbox.create starts the new record immediately.<br/>sandbox.start is also available later for a stopped or failed record.
    Handlers->>Supervisor: start(sandboxId, createSpec)
    Supervisor->>DB: Persist container_creating / start_requested
    Supervisor->>Driver: create(spec with workspace, state, secrets mounts)
    Driver-->>Supervisor: Managed container reference
    Supervisor->>DB: Persist container_created then container_starting
    Supervisor->>Driver: start(ref)
    Supervisor->>Driver: inspect(ref)
    Driver-->>Supervisor: running status
    Supervisor->>DB: Persist container_started / started
    Supervisor-->>Handlers: Running lifecycle record
    Handlers-->>UI: Created sandbox and current lifecycle state

    Agent->>Manager: Authenticated WebSocket upgrade and hello
    Manager->>DB: Load sandbox, session, and ingested event cursor
    Manager-->>Agent: welcome / resume decision
    Agent->>Manager: ready(status = booting)
    Manager->>DB: Persist connected session and daemon lifecycle
    Manager-->>UI: manager lifecycle event

    Operator->>UI: Invoke a sandbox operation
    UI->>Manager: Protocol request targeting<br/>{role: sandbox_agent, id: sandboxId}
    Manager->>Handlers: Parse catalog method, params, lineage, timeout, idempotency
    Handlers->>Handlers: Verify sandbox is ready for operations
    Handlers->>Agent: Forward the same method and params<br/>with correlation / causation / trace lineage
    Agent->>Agent: Execute via SandboxDaemon and host runtime
    Agent-->>Handlers: Correlated operation result or typed error
    Handlers-->>Manager: Preserve response semantics
    Manager-->>UI: Correlated response

    Agent->>Outbox: Append durable event with sandbox:<id> sequence
    Outbox->>Manager: Send event batch over Protocol v1
    Manager->>DB: Idempotently ingest durable event
    DB-->>Manager: Commit succeeded
    Manager-->>Agent: Processed ACK for sandbox:<id>
    Agent->>Outbox: Advance ACK cursor and compact when eligible
    Manager-->>UI: Deliver selected sandbox event
    UI->>Reducers: Apply event to browser state
    Reducers-->>Manager: Advance processed cursor / ACK after application

    alt UI reconnect cursor is replayable
        UI->>Manager: hello with processed stream cursors
        Manager->>DB: Read events after cursor while buffering live events
        Manager-->>UI: Ordered replay, then buffered live events
        UI->>Reducers: Apply replay atomically
    else Replay cannot satisfy the cursor
        Manager-->>UI: Snapshot recovery required
        UI->>Manager: Request manager/sandbox recovery snapshot
        Manager->>DB: Build snapshot and authoritative cursors
        Manager-->>UI: Snapshot + atomic cursor installation data
        UI->>Reducers: Replace projected state, then resume live stream
    end

    Note over Agent,DB: The manager acknowledges a durable agent event only after PostgreSQL ingestion.
    Note over UI,Reducers: The UI advances durable progress only after reducer/application succeeds.
